Sample_treatment_protocol_ch1: 50,000 T47D cells were treated with DMSO or BYL719 1μM for 24hr.
Sample_growth_protocol_ch1: T47D cells were maintained in RPMI 1640 with 10% FBS, 1% L-glutamine and 1% penicillin-streptomycin.
Sample_extract_protocol_ch1: 50,000 T47D cells were dissociated with acutase treatment and lysed with double the concentration of IGEPAL (0.2%) for successful library preparation., ATAC-seq libraries were prepared using Illumina's TruSeq ChIP sample prep.Libraries were validated using the Agient Technologies 2100 Bioanalyzer and Qubit high sensitivity assay.
Sample_data_processing: Starting from fastq files containing ATAC-seq paired-end reads, sequencing adaptors were removed using Trimmomatic., Trimmed reads were mapped to the hg19 human genome using Bowtie2 allowing at most 1 seed mismatch and keeping only uniquely aligned reads., Duplicates were removed using Picard., For peak-calling the read start sites were adjusted (reads aligning to the +/- strand were offset by +4bp/-5bp, respectively) to represent the center of the transposon binding-event., Peak calling was performed on each condition individually by pooling reads from biological replicates, and using MACS2 with a permissive P-value threshold (-p 1e-2).
Supplementary_files_format_and_content: bw files were generated using deeptools.
